***Factory***

*Definition*

- Used when a method return one of several possible classes that share
a common super class
- The class is chosen at runtime


*Usages*
- when you don't know ahead of time which object / class you will need
- when all the possible classes are in the same subclass level
- To make the code centralized in one place
- When you want to avoid user to know all classes that don't need
- to encapsulate the object creation

